Notebook[{
Cell["InfraPlane", "Title",ExpressionUUID->"e56bd6fc-9b23-471d-8c7c-d0cec0346e46"],

Cell["[LLM Generated]", "Subtitle",ExpressionUUID->"72d388bc-e308-4b57-9323-6e48cd51013b"],

Cell["\<\
InfraPlane is the wrapper head for bisecting-hyperplane vertex sets. \
InfraPlane[{set}] is the unary form; InfraPlane[{set1, \[Ellipsis], setk}] is \
the multi-realisation form. FindInfraBisectingHyperplane emits a List of unary \
InfraPlane[{set}] wrappers. Scene-language constructors InfraPlane[p1, p2] \
and InfraPlane[p1, p2, {lo, hi}] are used inside InfraScene.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"47c3723f-485e-46df-8dac-a7dc3e5ef62b"],

Cell["Setup", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"9779cff3-994a-4058-820e-7ec12c97a11a"],

